tip.text: Tucked inside Shibuya streets, this place is beyond amazing. The Japanese ambience coffee shop is exquisitely artistic. Try their charcoal roasted coffees, winner coffee, iced milk tea, chiffon cake.
The 'Kill Bill' inspired theme will surely satisfy not only your taste buds, but your vision as well. Try the course menu, excellent cuts of sashimi and delicious yaki-toris. A must-visit in Tokyo.
The new 'it' place for coffee. Try their salted caramel latte. You should also try their brownies: triple chocolate and lotus.
A true hidden gem! Loved every bit of it. Try their escargots, burrata with carpaccio, fried calamari with tomatoes & olives, foie grass pasta, duck with orange sauce. Their pear tart is to die for!
Impressive food. The coffee was really good. I came here for breakfast and I really loved the turkish eggs. Their dark chocolate cookie is to die for! The lunch/dinner menu looks interesting as well.
Try their lavender with white chocolate milk cake. Their coffee is really good too.
Another lovely coffee shop. Quite similar to Arabica, but I'm loving this more. In love with their logo though.
The famous café in London will surely leave a footprint here. People would come here for the milk cake and the other delicious desserts they offer. And yes you'll have to wait a lot to get there!
Loved the hot/cold tea and coffee selections. Love the fact that they have the soft green tea ice cream. Tried the egg puff, not bad. They just need to bring more selections of the bakery.
I can say that its the best burger in AD. I hope they maintain their good quality. Try the dangerous chicken slider with the moonshiner beef burger. As a side dish order their dynamite shrimps. Yum!
Cute and delicious food. Try their hilldog cheetos slider, buffy chicken burger, mac cheetos pasta.
Creative fusion food. Try their nigiri tuna, butterfed fried chicken burger, marinated chicken wings, spicy tuna maki, tempura maki. Desserts: karak ice cream.
Try their paratta with hot dog, cheese & cheetos with the iced karak.

A hidden gem. The food was superb. Try their schewan prawn spring rolls, fried baby corn with spring onions, prawns in burnt chili, shanghai chicken, prawns in crab sauce, vegetable fried rice.
Chocolate heaven. The best hot chocolate and dark chocolates ever!!

A top-notch restaurant in London. Try their crab donuts, grilled octopus starter, beef short ribs. The desserts are not to be missed: frozen apple panacata, pumpking custard, chocolate ganache.
A good spot for breakfast. Try their shakshouka, mushroom sourdough egg, corn cake with avocado.
Try their molten marshmallow hot chocolate and chocolate cookies sandwich.
Specialized for their delicious shakshoukas!

Never thought Filipino food would be that good! Try their spicy squid, gamba prawns, mixed seafood with special sauce, bbq beef ribs, adibo rice. Desserts: sapin sapin and halo halo.
An exceptional Indian restaurant. I would rate it the best Indian restaurant in Dubai. Try their beef short ribs, prawns w/ crispy garlic, butter chicken, lobster special. Desserts: rus malay.

One of the best restaurants in Seoul. Try their hot and sour soup, beef lettuce wrap, fried sichuan squids, shrimps in five spice sauce, sichuan crab rice. Loved the spices and chili. Warning: spicy!!
One of the best burgers I ever tried! Try their brooklyn and cheese skirt burgers. Their fries are out of the world!
A very cozy coffee shop with excellent coffees. Try their piccolo.

Amazing Indian restaurant. Try their king crab puri, chicken 65, fried calamari, mushroom croquettes, marinated chicken w/ burrata, black cod, coconut shrimps, seafood biryani. Desserts: the break up!

Amazing seafood restaurant. You must try their red shrimp basket, which was so delicious, and the king crab with spicy Singaporean sauce!
Another excellent Thai restaurant. Try their mixed appetizer platter, tom yum soup, pad thai, prawns with garlic sauce, woke fried beef with oyster sauce. Desserts: try the first item there.

Adored their food big time. Try their sweet corn chicken soup, prawn dumplings, sesame prawn toast, vegetable spring rolls, crispy schewan prawns, kung pao prawns, prawns fried rice with pineapple.

My favorite restaurant so far! Everything here will amaze you. Try their crispy duck salad, snails, lobster roll, crispy beef, truffle risotto, otoro, 16/20 sushi, corn. Desserts: walnut cheesecake.

tip.text: The decor was stunning, very classy, yet modern. Try their foie gras sliders, which was mouth-watering. Also, try their daviola pizza and their lobster linguine. Will definitely come back.

Owners of Jean-Georges, so you're expecting something special. Try their pecan salad, fried calamari, parmesan crusted chicken, fusseli arabiata. Desserts: salted caramel sundae, raspberry cheesecake.
Expected better but the food was good. Try their crab toast, salt & pepper shrimps, special sushi, shrimp avocado salad, truffle pizza, fried chicken. Desserts: salt & caramel sundae.
Loved the beef iskander. I would also recommend their mezze platter, grilled sujok, chicken doner. And of course try their kunafa with either turkish coffee or tea.

The concept is fantastic! You can now have delicious healthy food. Loved the fact that every dish has a calorie count. Try their salmon teriyaki, penne arabiata with shrimps, shitake mushroom salad.
